Foreign buyers will be charged a higher arms account when purchasing real estate in Britain
According to new conservation plans, foreign buyers will be charged a higher arms account when purchasing real estate in Britain, with additional funds to help homeless people.
This move will neutralize the success of Corbin's efforts to attract young voters
The increase in the arms commission will affect those who do not pay taxes in Britain
