Teresa May will announce today the decision for foreign buyers to pay a higher arms account in the purchase of real estate in Britain, with additional revenues going to help homeless people.
This move will be seen as an attempt to neutralize the success of Jeremy Corbin's efforts to attract young voters, promising more affordable housing and aimed at people with high incomes.
The increase in the arms account will affect individuals and companies who do not pay taxes in Britain, with additional revenues supporting the government's efforts to limit the number of people sleeping on the street.
